Honey.

02:08.529 --> 02:10.496
I know you're in shock,

02:10.497 --> 02:12.431
okay?

02:13.667 --> 02:16.168
big deal.
You'll live.

02:16.170 --> 02:18.337
You can think about
the meaning of life later,

02:18.339 --> 02:22.307
but right now,
we got shit to do.

02:22.309 --> 02:24.643
Okay?

02:24.645 --> 02:26.345
- Okay.
- Okay.

02:26.347 --> 02:28.247
All right.

02:28.249 --> 02:29.515
Go change.

02:52.539 --> 02:56.675
- I just killed someone, mother.

02:56.677 --> 02:59.211
- Well, you wanted
to know, Norman.

02:59.213 --> 03:01.280
You kept asking questions.

03:01.282 --> 03:03.382
You can't do this to me.

03:03.384 --> 03:05.250
You can't be like,
"i don't believe in Santa claus"

03:05.252 --> 03:06.652
and then when I say,
"okay, honey, you're right,"

03:06.654 --> 03:08.387
you freak out.

03:08.389 --> 03:10.689
I mean, this--this is not fair.
You painted me in a corner.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.959
And now you have to
deal with it, okay?

03:13.961 --> 03:16.595
- I'm trying.

03:16.597 --> 03:20.566
It's just a lot.

03:47.527 --> 03:49.995
- turn off the headlights.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.466
- what are they doing, mother?

03:56.704 --> 03:57.703
- Mm.

04:45.351 --> 04:47.819
- This is gonna be a long night.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.305
Okay.

05:06.307 --> 05:08.774
- That was a body bag.
Mother, did you see it?

05:08.776 --> 05:10.609
- It doesn't necessarily
have anything to do with us--

05:10.611 --> 05:13.378
- that was Jim, mother.
It was Jim Blackwell.

05:13.380 --> 05:14.780
Who else is it
gonna be in that lake?

05:14.782 --> 05:17.382
- Norman, you cannot have
a meltdown.

05:17.384 --> 05:18.784
- Sheriff Greene
has already come around,

05:18.786 --> 05:19.851
asking about him once before.

05:19.853 --> 05:21.520
She already suspects us

05:21.522 --> 05:23.555
of having something to do
with his disappearance,

05:23.557 --> 05:25.424
and she is gonna
piece it all together and--

05:38.572 --> 05:41.640
I'm gonna pretend that
didn't just happen right now.

05:43.877 --> 05:45.677
W-we have to focus

05:45.679 --> 05:48.080
on getting rid of Sam's body,
step by step.

05:48.082 --> 05:49.481
We deal with the rest later.

05:49.483 --> 05:50.882
We can't use the lake this time,

05:50.884 --> 05:52.884
so we have to choose between
the cliff and the woods.

05:52.886 --> 05:54.553
- "This time"?

05:56.757 --> 06:00.592
How many times
have we done this, mother?

06:00.594 --> 06:03.762
How many bodies are
they gonna find in that lake?

06:11.572 --> 06:13.572
Norman,

06:13.574 --> 06:16.441
there is a lot at stake
right now.

06:16.443 --> 06:18.577
If they connect
these crimes to you,

06:18.579 --> 06:20.846
they are either going
to kill you

06:20.848 --> 06:23.448
or they are gonna put you
in a mental institution

06:23.450 --> 06:26.785
and they are gonna
feed you meds!

06:26.787 --> 06:29.855
Whichever it is, it's
gonna be the end of us.

06:36.530 --> 06:40.165
Let's just dump the body
in the woods.

06:40.167 --> 06:42.601
Okay, I mean, we still
have to get rid of the car;

06:42.603 --> 06:44.436
we have to
clean the crime scene.

06:44.438 --> 06:46.805
We--you don't have time
for this emotional bullshit.

06:46.807 --> 06:48.774
Come on!
Let's go.

06:55.983 --> 06:57.883
God.

06:57.885 --> 07:01.720
Man, can't see shit
in the snow.

07:03.524 --> 07:06.191
I know there's an
old well here somewhere.

07:06.193 --> 07:07.592
- How do you know these things?

07:07.594 --> 07:09.795
I have eyes in my head.

07:09.797 --> 07:10.896
- So do I, mother.

07:10.898 --> 07:12.564
It's not like
i make a mental note

07:12.566 --> 07:14.199
of good things
to drop bodies into.

07:14.201 --> 07:15.500
- Yeah, well, who's talking now?

07:15.502 --> 07:16.568
- That doesn't even make sense.

07:16.570 --> 07:18.470
- Sh--you know what I mean.

07:18.472 --> 07:21.873
It's good that one of us is
thinking about these things.

07:25.845 --> 07:27.712
God.

07:27.714 --> 07:29.448
He's so heavy.

07:29.450 --> 07:30.882
- Yeah, well, he's tall.

07:30.884 --> 07:32.918
Was tall.

07:32.920 --> 07:36.555
- All right.

07:36.557 --> 07:37.656
One,

07:37.658 --> 07:38.523
two,

07:38.525 --> 07:40.592
three!

07:49.536 --> 07:51.036
This doesn't seem real.

07:52.673 --> 07:54.806
I can't believe I did this.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.975
He didn't deserve to die.

07:59.213 --> 08:00.846
- Jesus, Norman.

08:09.223 --> 08:11.957
if I had a quarter,
I'd make a wish.

08:13.494 --> 08:15.894
we gotta
ditch the car now.

08:30.710 --> 08:32.277
Jesus.

08:32.279 --> 08:35.714
Walking in this cold
for five miles.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.649
- You can't control
the weather, mother.

08:37.650 --> 08:41.086
That's one thing you have
nothing to say about.

08:41.087 --> 08:44.656
- Your money's falling
out of your pocket.

08:46.726 --> 08:49.561
- Can't believe he gave us
all of this for the car.

08:49.563 --> 08:51.530
- What'd you think
a chop shop was?

08:51.532 --> 08:53.665
They chop up stolen cars
and they sell the parts.

08:53.667 --> 08:55.901
Of course they gave you money.

08:55.903 --> 08:57.736
- It's just...

08:57.738 --> 08:59.304
Chick didn't give me any money

08:59.306 --> 09:00.772
for the other car, that's all.

09:00.774 --> 09:03.275
That guy.

09:04.311 --> 09:06.878
You have a lot to learn, Norman.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.047
- I know, mother.

09:09.049 --> 09:10.916
I do.

09:12.019 --> 09:13.018
- now we just got to finish

09:13.020 --> 09:15.287
micro-cleaning the motel room.

09:15.289 --> 09:18.023
Hope I remember
where I put the luminol.

09:19.593 --> 09:21.660
what'd I do with it?

09:25.832 --> 09:27.666
- mother.

09:27.668 --> 09:28.900
- Yeah?

09:28.902 --> 09:32.037
- Should I just turn myself in?

09:32.039 --> 09:34.873
- How can you say that to me?

09:34.875 --> 09:37.075
- Mother, I don't want
to be taken away from you

09:37.077 --> 09:38.343
or killed or locked up,

09:38.345 --> 09:40.812
but what we are doing is wrong.

09:42.583 --> 09:43.782
- you know,
maybe I shouldn't have

09:43.784 --> 09:45.784
told you the truth
about how things work.

09:45.786 --> 09:47.786
Maybe--maybe
it's just too much.

09:50.891 --> 09:54.125
look, if you ever
feel overwhelmed,

09:54.127 --> 09:57.362
I could just...
You know, take over.

09:57.364 --> 09:58.964
I would be happy to do it.
- No.

09:58.966 --> 10:01.900
Mother, no, that is
not an option.

10:01.902 --> 10:04.803
Okay?
Never again.

10:11.812 --> 10:14.079
shit.

10:14.081 --> 10:16.381
I'll handle this.

10:16.383 --> 10:18.383
- Don't do anything
stupid, Norman.

10:18.385 --> 10:21.019
If you love me.

10:27.194 --> 10:29.928
- Oh. Hello.

10:33.132 --> 10:36.701
Yeah, I thought I heard someone.

10:36.703 --> 10:39.771
- Hope I didn't catch you
at a bad time.

10:39.773 --> 10:41.940
- Oh, no, no,
no trouble at all.

10:41.942 --> 10:43.074
No, today's linen day.

10:43.076 --> 10:45.410
I always change the beds
here once a week,

10:45.412 --> 10:47.846
whether they've
been used or not.

10:47.848 --> 10:51.049
- Well, I've just been down at
the little lake down the road.

10:51.051 --> 10:52.150
Do you know the one?

10:53.153 --> 10:55.887
- Uh--yeah.

10:55.889 --> 10:57.122
Yes, i--i do, I think so.

10:57.124 --> 11:00.158
Is--it's over, uh,
over that way, huh?

11:00.160 --> 11:03.161
Yes. Yes, i-i often send
the kayakers there

11:03.163 --> 11:05.797
during the summer months.

11:05.799 --> 11:10.068
- Well, we found multiple bodies
there last night.

11:11.438 --> 11:13.038
- dead bodies?

11:13.040 --> 11:15.206
- Yes.

11:15.208 --> 11:18.209
And one was Jim Blackwell's.

11:22.049 --> 11:25.150
- oh, well, i--i--i don't
know what to say, sheriff.

11:25.152 --> 11:28.053
That's--that's truly awful news.

11:29.056 --> 11:30.055
- yes, it is.

11:36.263 --> 11:37.896
I just thought you should know

11:37.898 --> 11:40.899
Jim Blackwell
won't be bothering you.

11:44.705 --> 11:48.006
still like to know why
he had your address.

11:48.008 --> 11:50.208
And what Alex romero

11:50.210 --> 11:52.077
might have to do with
any of this.

11:52.079 --> 11:54.946
- I--i--just--i can't imagine.

11:58.919 --> 12:02.020
- looks like someone
left here in a hurry.

12:04.191 --> 12:05.757
- oh.

12:05.759 --> 12:08.026
Yeah, that, that was a...

12:08.028 --> 12:09.160
An unruly guest.

12:09.162 --> 12:10.462
I--i guess

12:10.464 --> 12:12.063
raking the gravel is next up.

12:12.065 --> 12:15.200
- I thought you said you
hadn't had any guests?

12:15.202 --> 12:18.036
- Really, did...

12:18.038 --> 12:20.105
The--oh, linen, and the--
no, i--i mean,

12:20.107 --> 12:23.775
we haven't had any real guests
that we--

12:23.777 --> 12:25.944
I mean, we had someone,
some people that came by,

12:25.946 --> 12:27.312
but it was only
a couple of hours.

12:27.314 --> 12:29.147
It was a...
Yeah.

12:29.149 --> 12:30.515
It was a quick one, you know?

12:30.517 --> 12:31.950
I had no idea that's
what they were gonna do.

12:31.952 --> 12:34.953
They did pay for the full night,
sheriff, so.

12:34.955 --> 12:38.323
- I know you're not
like that, Norman.

12:38.325 --> 12:41.292
But when was this?

12:41.294 --> 12:42.961
- Uh, this?

12:42.963 --> 12:45.263
It was, uh,

12:45.265 --> 12:46.898
it was last night.

12:48.935 --> 12:51.269
- well, I hope they didn't
give you too much trouble.

12:51.271 --> 12:53.304
- Oh, no.
No, no, no.

12:56.176 --> 12:57.542
- all right, then, Norman,

12:57.544 --> 12:59.544
I'll let you get back
to your linen.

12:59.546 --> 13:00.845
- And the raking.

13:00.847 --> 13:02.914
- And the raking, yes.

13:02.916 --> 13:05.183
Take care, now.
- All righty, sheriff.

14:11.951 --> 14:14.219
- What are you looking for?

14:14.221 --> 14:15.553
- I just--i wanted some water.

14:15.555 --> 14:17.222
I thought there was
a--a glass in here somewhere.

14:17.224 --> 14:18.923
- I'll get you a glass of water.

14:18.925 --> 14:20.225
Get back in bed.

14:20.227 --> 14:23.461
You've hardly eaten
for three days.

14:23.463 --> 14:24.596
You feel hungry yet?

14:24.598 --> 14:25.930
- Yeah, actually, I am.

14:25.932 --> 14:27.332
- Okay.

14:36.942 --> 14:39.277
Okay, okay, slow down.

14:39.279 --> 14:41.312
There's more.

14:44.350 --> 14:46.484
- Did i--did I have anything
with me when I got here?

14:46.486 --> 14:49.554
It--everything is just
such a blur.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.623
- Nope.
No, just you.

14:51.625 --> 14:53.491
Well, and a big, infected wound.

14:53.493 --> 14:57.629
I got some antibiotics.
That's what you've been taking.

14:57.631 --> 15:00.031
- Thanks.

15:00.033 --> 15:01.966
I'm pretty sure
you saved my life.

15:01.968 --> 15:04.903
- That was my goal.

15:09.508 --> 15:11.509
- I know I had a gun with me.

15:11.511 --> 15:13.311
Where is it?

15:15.282 --> 15:18.516
- You must have dropped it.

15:21.087 --> 15:22.453
finish your food.

15:22.455 --> 15:24.589
I'll be back in a little bit
to clear it up.

15:49.014 --> 15:51.115
- what'd she say?

15:51.117 --> 15:52.650
What are you doing, Norman?

15:56.022 --> 15:58.556
- they found more than one body.

15:58.558 --> 15:58.556
Multiple bodies.

15:58.558 --> 16:02.060
- Well, we kind of knew
that was gonna happen.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.695
- But it's all connected to us.

16:03.697 --> 16:06.397
They're gonna investigate
and we'll be on the radar.

16:06.399 --> 16:08.700
They could even
search the house.

16:08.702 --> 16:11.402
And so,

16:11.404 --> 16:13.571
we have to get everything
out of here

16:13.573 --> 16:17.976
that could possibly
arouse suspicion.

16:20.447 --> 16:21.579
- okay.

16:25.552 --> 16:28.987
so what--what are we
gonna do with...

16:28.989 --> 16:32.423
Where we gonna put her?

16:32.425 --> 16:36.394
- A spot in the woods,
up the mountain pass.

16:36.396 --> 16:38.396
There'll be snow there,

16:38.398 --> 16:40.665
and there's that
beautiful little clearing

16:40.667 --> 16:42.467
by the abandoned cabin.

16:42.469 --> 16:44.002
We found it there once
when we were

16:44.004 --> 16:45.403
collecting foliage on an out--
- yeah, whatever.

16:45.405 --> 16:46.471
Let's just get it done.

16:46.473 --> 16:47.638
- Maybe you should go

16:47.640 --> 16:50.074
back down to the motel
for a while.

16:52.178 --> 16:55.113
Put up a new shower curtain
or something.

16:57.784 --> 17:00.752
- I see.

17:00.754 --> 17:03.121
Okay. Yeah.

17:04.624 --> 17:06.523
sure.

18:52.564 --> 18:55.299
- I'll be back for you
as soon as I can.

18:55.301 --> 18:56.734
I promise.

18:59.305 --> 19:02.173
I love you.

20:24.591 --> 20:27.225
- I'll, uh,
make us something to eat.

20:27.227 --> 20:29.760
- Okay.

21:20.646 --> 21:23.347
you've been living here
alone all this time?

21:23.349 --> 21:25.349
- Uh, yes.

21:25.351 --> 21:26.884
Yeah, I, uh, I get by.

21:26.886 --> 21:30.755
- Norman, you shou--
you should have called me.

21:30.757 --> 21:32.990
You shouldn't be
living here by yourself.

21:32.992 --> 21:37.028
- I--it's--it's okay.
The motel's still running.

21:41.400 --> 21:44.468
Oh, how's Emma?

21:44.470 --> 21:46.003
- Uh, she's good.

21:46.005 --> 21:48.005
- Yeah?

21:48.007 --> 21:50.775
- We, uh, we got married.

21:50.777 --> 21:54.979
And, um, and we have a baby.

21:54.981 --> 21:57.481
- You--a baby?

21:57.483 --> 22:00.051
- Yeah.
Yeah, a--a little girl.

22:00.053 --> 22:01.919
Katie.

22:09.062 --> 22:11.362
A girl.

22:22.974 --> 22:26.043
I'm so sorry.

22:26.045 --> 22:28.713
I'm so sorry that
i didn't call you.

22:28.715 --> 22:30.448
That I haven't
seen you for so long.

22:30.450 --> 22:33.084
It's just...

22:33.086 --> 22:34.452
You have no idea, Dylan.

22:34.454 --> 22:36.954
Every day is a small century.

22:59.045 --> 23:01.779
- are you still
seeing your doctor?

23:01.781 --> 23:04.081
- Hm?
My doctor?

23:04.083 --> 23:06.417
- Yeah, your therapist?

23:06.419 --> 23:09.453
- Oh. Dr. Edwards.

23:09.455 --> 23:11.088
No, not officially anymore.

23:11.090 --> 23:13.991
Although I did happen to
bump into him in the village

23:13.993 --> 23:17.461
just this week and,
you know, he's doing well.

23:17.463 --> 23:19.997
- Whe--when did you
stop seeing him?

23:21.134 --> 23:23.834
- after mother died.

23:23.836 --> 23:25.403
It was all too much.

23:28.141 --> 23:30.040
- Are you still taking the meds?

23:32.011 --> 23:33.778
- no, no, I...

23:33.780 --> 23:35.413
Haven't for a while
now, actually.

23:35.415 --> 23:37.515
I really don't think
that I need them.

23:57.903 --> 24:00.871
The only thing is that

24:00.873 --> 24:04.041
I do sometimes miss our mother.

24:06.913 --> 24:10.948
So very much, Dylan.
I can't even tell you.

24:10.950 --> 24:13.117
It's just not the same,

24:13.119 --> 24:14.919
and it never will be.

24:25.064 --> 24:27.565
- I don't think
you're well, Norman.

24:30.102 --> 24:32.503
I don't think you should be
living here alone.

24:32.505 --> 24:34.605
- Well, living anywhere else,

24:34.607 --> 24:38.108
any other way is not an option.

24:44.984 --> 24:47.251
- look, I'm gonna, uh,
I'm gonna stay here with you

24:47.253 --> 24:49.520
for a few days.

24:49.522 --> 24:52.189
Okay, and we're gonna
get this all figured out.

24:59.198 --> 25:01.031
- I, uh,

25:01.033 --> 25:02.500
I don't feel so good.

25:02.502 --> 25:05.102
I'm just gonna go upstairs
and lie down.

25:05.104 --> 25:08.005
But enjoy.
Make yourself at home.

